ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Some of the buyers attribute at least <em>part<=
/em> of the
turnaround, improbably, to <strong>Linda Yaccarino</strong>, whom Elon hire=
d away from NBCU in May 2023 to become X=E2=80=99s C.E.O. Since then, she h=
as unveiled a number of subscription-based products that seem to be working=
=2E She has also, somehow, managed to l=
ure advertisers back to the platform.=20=
(Though she has certainly benefited from the fact that few companies want t=
o pick a fight with Musk these days, given his ubiquity, including in the W=
hite House.) Meanwhile, X is also benefiting from Meta=E2=80=99s
removal of many controls on <em>its</em> social media platforms, too, offer=
ing advertisers a similarly brand-unsafe experience. Direct X competitors T=
hreads and Bluesky haven=E2=80=99t quite cracked the code. TikTok has its o=
wn existential crisis, obviously. So there aren=E2=80=99t many better optio=
ns.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I=E2=80=99ve heard from someone directly involved i=
n the debt transactions that no less than <em>99 percent</em> of the
advertisers have returned (perhaps this person was being hyperbolic; there =
are still a lot of nutty advertisements in my feed), and that there are now=
 more than 3 million paid =E2=80=9Cpremium=E2=80=9D subscribers on top of X=
=E2=80=99s 220 million or so daily users. December 2024 revenue, I=E2=80=99=
m told, was up 40 percent from the same period the previous year, with adve=
rtising revenue up 32 percent year over year and the balance of the increas=
e coming from paid premium subscriptions.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">
<br/>Linda, it seems, is actually doing a pretty good job=E2=80=94and appea=
rs to have evolved since that awful blink-twice <strong>Kara Swisher </stro=
ng><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2U=
ktxclJLZ0dWRnEwMFNPd09zQ2ZjOTlwTFNTQT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3Mu=
Y29tLzIwMjMvMTAvMDUvY29tbXVuaWNhdGlvbi1sZXNzb25zLWZyb20teC1jZW8tbGluZGEteWF=
jY2FyaW5vLWNvZGUtYXBwZWFyYW5jZT91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249VGhlK0Jlc3QrJTI2K1RoZStCcm=
